  "response": "In the 1912 U.S. presidential election, the major candidates were Woodrow Wilson (Democrat), Theodore Roosevelt (Progressive), and William Howard Taft (Republican). Here are the estimated campaign expenditures for each candidate:\n\n- **Woodrow Wilson (Democrat)**: Approximately $1 million.\n- **Theodore Roosevelt (Progressive)**: Approximately $2 million.\n- **William Howard Taft (Republican)**: Approximately $1 million.\n\nIt's important to note that campaign finance in 1912 was quite different from today, and these figures reflect the expenditures of the campaigns at that time, which were significantly lower than modern election costs.",
